/td>\n<td style=\"padding:10px 0;color:#fbbf24;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;\">42/100</td>\n<td style=\"padding:10px 0;\"><span style=\"background:#2d2200;color:#fbbf24;font-size:10px;font-weight:600;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;\">MODERATE</span></td>\n<td style=\"padding:10px 0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">Stop breached &middot; AI thesis intact &middot; Strong analyst support $190 &middot; Jul 25 deadline</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- IBKR INTELLIGENCE -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:14px 24px 6px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#475569;font-size:10px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;font-weight:600;\">&#9656; IBKR Intelligence</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"background:#0a0f1a;border-left:3px solid #334155;padding:14px 24px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#475569;font-size:12px;\">&#128202; IBKR connector offline this run &#8212; performance data (TWR/MWR), allocation breakdown, and investment themes unavailable. Connect IBKR to restore full intelligence layer in tomorrow&#8217;s email.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- UPCOMING CALENDAR -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:14px 24px;border-top:1px solid #334155;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 8px;color:#f8fafc;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;\">&#128197; Upcoming</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#fbbf24;font-size:12px;\">&#128276; Jul 4 &#8212; NYSE Closed (Independence Day)</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#ef4444;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;\">&#128680; Jul 7 (Mon) &#8212; VERA PDUFA. FDA can act any time. Keep phone close. Check IBKR app every few hours.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">Jul 8+ &#8212; Enter CAPR (~$24&#8211;26) IF VERA approved. Halal check first.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#fbbf24;font-size:12px;\">Jul 17 &#8212; CELC PDUFA (research this weekend if VERA approved)</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 4px;color:#fbbf24;font-size:12px;\">Jul 25 &#8212; ANET HARD EXIT DEADLINE (before Q2 earnings ~Aug 5)</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#94a3b8;font-size:12px;\">Jul 29 &#8212; CAPR AdCom</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- EDUCATION -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:14px 24px 6px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#475569;font-size:10px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;font-weight:600;\">&#9656; Today&#8217;s Concept</p>\n</td></tr>\n<tr><td style=\"background:#1e293b;padding:22px 24px;border-top:1px solid #334155;border-left:3px solid #8b5cf6;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 3px;color:#a78bfa;font-size:10px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;\">Concept #15 of 30 &#8212; Semiconductors</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 14px;color:#f8fafc;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;\">Process Node Transitions</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 12px;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;\">Every 18&#8211;24 months, TSMC launches a new process node &#8212; 7nm &#8594; 5nm &#8594; 3nm &#8594; 2nm &#8594; A16. Smaller nodes pack more transistors per mm&#178;, cut power, and improve performance per watt. Each step is a step-function jump, not a marginal tweak, because the underlying lithography (ASML&#8217;s EUV machines at $380M each, multi-year backlog) is being upgraded. That scarcity constraint is exactly why TSMC has pricing power: you literally cannot &#8220;order more 3nm chips&#8221; on short notice &#8212; you get in line behind Apple and NVDA.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 12px;color:#cbd5e1;font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;\"><strong style=\"color:#f8fafc;\">Your ANET position:</strong> Arista&#8217;s next-gen EtherLink ASICs &#8212; the silicon running the 800G switching fabric inside AI data centers &#8212; are taped out on TSMC&#8217;s 3nm node, cutting latency and power vs the previous 5nm generation. When TSMC opens 3nm capacity to ANET, they can build chips that literally weren&#8217;t manufacturable before. That&#8217;s the hard floor under the AI ethernet narrative. NVDA &#8594; TSMC &#8594; ASML is the same supply chain, one level deeper &#8212; track node-capacity news the same way you track hyperscaler capex: it&#8217;s your upstream leading indicator.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#7c3aed;font-size:11px;border-top:1px solid #334155;padding-top:10px;\">&#128218; Also today: <em>Tape-out</em> &#8212; when chip designers send the design file to the foundry for manufacturing. No going back after this; engineers wait 3&#8211;6 months for first silicon. This is why chip product launches are planned 12&#8211;18 months before the chip ships.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<tr><td style=\"background:#0f172a;padding:14px 24px;border-top:1px solid #1e293b;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 3px;color:#475569;font-size:10px;\">&#128197; Report: Thursday, July 3, 2026 &middot; Kuwait (AST, UTC+3) &middot; Post-market</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 3px;color:#475569;font-size:10px;\">&#128185; Prices: Web-sourced (Yahoo Finance / CNBC data) &#8212; IBKR connector offline. VERA close estimated; verify exact price in broker app before any decisions.</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#3b4a5a;font-size:9px;margin-top:6px;\">Automated research, not financial advice. Halal compliance per AAOIFI standards. Verify new entries on Musaffa before trading.</p>\n</td></tr>\n\n</table>\n</td></tr>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>\n"\n}